Long gashes run diagonally across this ghost's torso. His throat is a large and gaping wound.

Crafted from fine dwarven leathers, this light armor is traditonally worn by respected herdkeepers. Its intent is not to protect the wearer in battle but to keep at bay the thorns and thistles of the wild and the occasional bite of an angered animal.
This proud Elkenbeast gazes around at its surroundings skittishly. Scorch marks rim a ragged hole in its gut and the smell of burnt flesh hangs thick about it.
This delicate hide is that of the northern elkenbeast. Their herds once dominated the northern mountains but hunting has reduced their numbers substantially.
Though it seems to harbor no ill intent towards you, this strange creature has taken a definite interest in your belongings.
The Night Hag's pale green face emerges from the mists, a welcome sight after the perils of the Barrier. She seems ageless here, neither old nor young, only weary from her efforts on your behalf.
